00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:40,464
Her name ain't Precious.

245
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:44,210
I want my money back
on this here ticket,

246
00:13:44,211 --> 00:13:45,803
and I want you to send
this here telegram.

247
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:48,848
Trip delayed, but I'm
coming real soon.

248
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,214
You just lie down in
the seat and be quiet.

249
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:25,009
Folks don't take to children
when they're doing business.

250
00:14:59,652 --> 00:15:01,045
- Yes?
- Good afternoon, madam.

251
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,854
Is Mr Rudolf Morgan
at home, please?

252
00:15:02,855 --> 00:15:03,855
Mr Morgan?

253
00:15:03,856 --> 00:15:06,717
Yes, madam. My name
is Pray, Moses Pray,

254
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:08,552
Kansas Bible Company. He'll know.

255
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:11,639
Oh, I'm sorry. Mr
Morgan has passed on.

256
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:14,183
Oh, madam, I'm... I just...

257
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:15,392
I don't know what to say.

258
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:17,353
What was it you were
seeing him about?

259
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,037
Well, he ordered this
here bible from...

260
00:15:19,038 --> 00:15:21,106
- Bible?
- Rudolph ordered a bible?

261
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,575
Yeah, he ordered this
here deluxe edition

262
00:15:22,576 --> 00:15:23,745
with the lady's
name in the corner.

263
00:15:23,746 --> 00:15:25,027
Lady's name?

264
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:27,696
Oh, I expect some special
gift for a family friend.

265
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:28,989
But under the circumstances,

266
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,241
I'll just give you back Mr
Morgan's dollar deposit,

267
00:15:31,347 --> 00:15:33,285
and there won't be no
further obligation.

268
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,153
Madam, I just don't
know how to put into

269
00:15:35,154 --> 00:15:36,830
words the sense of
sorrow that I feel.

270
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,833
What, what... what
name is in the corner?

271
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:41,893
I don't really know
what name Mr...

272
00:15:41,894 --> 00:15:44,213
Morgan had put in
the corner, madam.

273
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:45,422
Let's see, now.

274
00:15:45,527 --> 00:15:47,841
It's here somewhere. I've got it.

275
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,134
Here it is.

276
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:50,844
- Pearl...
- Pearl.

277
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,262
I'm Pearl.

278
00:15:52,368 --> 00:15:55,641
Well, he must have got this
here good book for you, madam.

279
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:58,018
Yes. Yes, he bought it for me.

280
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:00,270
Of course, now, you're
not obliged to take it.

281
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,897
Of course I'll take it.

282
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:03,732
There's just one
thing. You see, I...

283
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:05,859
I told him that I could
sell him a cheaper bible,

284
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:07,894
but no, naturally he
wanted the best, the

285
00:16:07,895 --> 00:16:09,822
best, of course, being
the deluxe edition

286
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:12,324
with the lady's name printed in
child-in-the-manger gold letters.

287
00:16:12,429 --> 00:16:13,742
Oh, he would.

288
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:16,829
Bringing a balance due
of... $8.00? $8.00.

289
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:18,372
$8.00?

290
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:21,417
Well, that's, $8.00 minus
the dollar deposit,

291
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:23,335
making it $7.00.

292
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,837
I'll go get my purse.

293
00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:26,790
Well, you're not obliged
to take it, now.

294
00:16:26,791 --> 00:16:27,840
Of course I'm obliged.

295
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:30,592
He ordered the deluxe.

296
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:35,264
But cold or no cold, it's good
to be back in old Manhattan.

297
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:38,183
Well, tell me, Jack, you've been
in town now since Thursday.

298
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:39,739
What have you been
doing with yourself?

299
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:40,894
Oh, I've had a lot of fun, Don.

300
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,439
I saw some shows, went to
a couple of nightclubs,

301
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,485
and last night, I
was invited over to

302
00:16:45,486 --> 00:16:47,276
Fred Allen's apartment for dinner.

303
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:48,381
Oh, Fred Allen?

304
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,112
Yeah, he and I are
pretty good friends now.

305
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:53,365
Well, I'm glad to hear it. Has
Fred got a nice apartment?

306
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,159
Oh, how could I tell, Don,

307
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:58,849
with all that laundry
hanging in the living room?

308
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:03,208
Ain't you gonna go to sleep?

309
00:17:03,814 --> 00:17:05,794
Don't you want to hear Jack Benny?

310
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:07,755
No.

311
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,840
I don't want to sound catty...

312
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:44,401
You're too young to
smoke. You're going

313
00:17:44,402 --> 00:17:46,126
to set this whole place on fire.

314
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:15,072
I now owe you $103.72.

315
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:19,076
Seventy-four.

