00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:23,038
♪ I always knew ♪

317
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:25,249
♪ Someday I'd accompany you ♪

318
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:29,419
♪ Along Flirtation Walk ♪

319
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,672
♪ A dream foretold ♪

320
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,841
♪ A story that you would unfold ♪

321
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:39,221
♪ That lives forever
and never grows old ♪

322
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:41,348
♪ I always felt ♪

323
00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:43,642
♪ That your little
heart would melt ♪

324
00:18:43,747 --> 00:18:45,269
♪ Along Flirtation Walk ♪

325
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:48,063
Frank D. Roosevelt said we're
all feeling a lot better.

326
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,857
He did, did he?

327
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:52,036
Made me feel good
when he said that.

328
00:18:52,037 --> 00:18:53,610
Better than I've
felt in a long time.

329
00:18:53,715 --> 00:18:56,155
Bet old Frank sure
does wish he was 21.

330
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:01,577
You don't like me, do you?

331
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:05,581
No, I don't like you.

332
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:13,797
Yes?

333
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:16,717
Afternoon, madam. I was wondering
if Mr Bates might be at home.

334
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,845
Mr Bates is dead. He
died over a week ago.

335
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,430
Oh, you mean he
passed over, madam?

336
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:24,057
Why, I was just talking to him
not less than a month ago.

337
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:25,809
- What was it you wanted?
- Well...

338
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:28,312
My name is Pray,
Kansas Bible Company.

339
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,439
I'm just here to deliver this
bible that Mr Bates ordered.

340
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:31,690
Bible?

341
00:19:31,795 --> 00:19:33,650
Who is it? What's the trouble?

342
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:37,154
Something about Benjamin
buying a bible.

343
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:39,114
Bible? What kind of bible?

344
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:42,117
He said he talked to Benjamin,
less than a month ago.

345
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:44,870
Well, I'm not exactly
sure of the dates, madam.

346
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:46,830
Well, I don't see how.

347
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:48,806
Benjamin didn't go
nowhere near that shop

348
00:19:48,807 --> 00:19:50,459
for more than a month
before he died.

349
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:53,253
Well, I may be a little
mixed up on the dates.

350
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:55,422
What company you say you're from?

351
00:19:55,527 --> 00:19:57,799
The Kansas Bible
Company, out of Wichita.

352
00:19:57,905 --> 00:19:59,509
Kansas Bible Company?

353
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:01,553
I ain't never heard of
no Kansas Bible Company.

354
00:20:01,658 --> 00:20:02,888
Daddy...

355
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:06,808
Can't we go now? I want to get
to church and pray for Mama.

356
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:11,271
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Sure we can, honey.

357
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:13,023
Daddy was just fixing to leave.

358
00:20:13,128 --> 00:20:15,943
This here is my little girl.
It's just the two of us now.

359
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:18,987
- My Mama's gone to the Lord.
- Oh, so has poor Mr Bates, honey.

360
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:21,073
I'll just, give you back
his dollar deposit,

361
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:23,533
and you let us know if
there's anything we can do.

362
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:26,411
Hold on, there. Wait
one damn minute.

363
00:20:29,019 --> 00:20:30,707
He actually done
ordered a bible, huh?

364
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,345
He sure did. Here
it is, right here

365
00:20:32,346 --> 00:20:33,877
in gold for somebody
named "Marie".

366
00:20:33,982 --> 00:20:35,542
That's her. She's Marie.

367
00:20:35,543 --> 00:20:37,881
Oh, she sure did
mean a lot to him.

368
00:20:37,986 --> 00:20:40,425
He especially had me get
the deluxe edition.

369
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:42,664
- How much to keep this here book?
- Oh, well, that one is the...

370
00:20:42,665 --> 00:20:44,096
It's the $12 one, Daddy.

371
00:20:44,201 --> 00:20:45,931
- $12?
- $12?

372
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:48,475
Yeah, well, honey, we have to have
a little goodness in our hearts,

373
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:49,973
I mean, considering
the circumstances.

374
00:20:49,974 --> 00:20:51,061
Never mind the circumstances.

375
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:54,815
And if it'll make that
woman happy, I'll take it.

376
00:21:07,307 --> 00:21:11,331
You owe me $85.74.

377
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:20,466
I mean, we're going to
Washington on the QT.

378
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:23,738
Molly, she says we
can't go on the QT,

379
00:21:23,739 --> 00:21:25,739
we've got to take
the Pennsylvania.

380
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:27,931
Hey, I'd better get going.

381
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:29,725
Hey, Molly, where's my
suitcase? Do you know?

382
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:31,935
I'm sure I don't know, McGee.
You had it last night.

383
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,354
Oh, I know where it is. It's
right here in the hall...

384
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:36,523
He's going to open the closet.

385
00:21:44,219 --> 00:21:46,867
Now he's going to say how he's got
to straighten the closet out.

386
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:49,494
Got to straighten out that
closet one of these days.

387
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:52,456
How'd you like to do a
little business with me?

388
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:55,125
You mean instead
of paying me back?

389
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:56,631
Now, don't get nervous.
I'll pay you back.

390
00:21:56,632 --> 00:21:58,031
I'm just saying, while
we're heading east,

391
00:21:58,032 --> 00:22:00,225
how'd you like to do a little
business together, that's all?

392
00:22:02,904 --> 00:22:04,103
Well, you're looking
at me like I'm

393
00:22:04,104 --> 00:22:05,135
out to cheat you or something.

394
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,512
I am offering you a business
proposition. Take it or leave it.

395
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:09,232
And turn off that
radio. You're like

396
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:10,891
to drive us all deaf
with that radio.

397
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:15,604
In an average way, of course.

398
00:22:21,381 --> 00:22:23,695
Ok, I want you to
remember one thing:

399
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,238
I decide on the price.

400
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:26,837
Maybe you don't know
French, but there's

401
00:22:26,838 --> 00:22:28,367
something in this world
called "finesse".

402
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:30,452
$12. I never sold
no bible for $12.

403
00:22:30,557 --> 00:22:32,704
That man was a law officer. You
could've had me put me in jail.

404
00:22:33,226 --> 00:22:34,623
We got it, didn't we?

405
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:38,293
I don't care if we got it. Don't
you go making the decisions.

406
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:40,404
I make the decisions.
All you got to

407
00:22:40,405 --> 00:22:42,464
do is look like a
pretty little girl.

408
00:22:47,407 --> 00:22:50,514
You ain't got something like a
ribbon in that cigar box, do you?

409
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:54,518
I got my mum's kimono in my
suitcase, Chinamen with umbrellas.

410
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:58,105
That ain't quite
what I had in mind.

411
00:23:07,177 --> 00:23:09,282
You look real nice in that ribbon.

412
00:23:09,388 --> 00:23:11,701
First off, I didn't know
was she a boy or a girl?

413
00:23:11,807 --> 00:23:13,161
I'm a girl.

414
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:15,831
Well, it makes all the difference.

415
00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:18,875
Ain't she got a sweet
little face, somehow.

416
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:20,462
Well, seeing how I
just got paid today,

417
00:23:20,463 --> 00:23:21,795
we'll take a ribbon
in each colour.

418
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,171
How much that going
to set me back?

419
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:25,340
Well, that'll be 15 cents.

420
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:29,136
Bought my grandchildren ribbons
just like this last holiday time.

421
00:23:29,241 --> 00:23:31,555
Grandchildren? I don't believe it.

422
00:23:31,566 --> 00:23:32,566
You break a five?

423
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,474
Well, you can believe
it, all right.

424
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:36,726
I'm just as old as I look.

425
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:38,937
Well, now, here you be.

426
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:43,316
That's one, two,
three, four, five.

427
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:45,402
This old wallet of mine is
about to bust its sides.

428
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:47,988
I'll give you five ones back,
you give me that $5 bill.

429
00:23:48,093 --> 00:23:49,656
How many grandchildren
you got altogether?

430
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:51,692
Well, I got two little
granddaughters,

431
00:23:51,693 --> 00:23:53,326
a nine-year-old, a ten-year-old,

432
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:55,996
two grandsons near 16,

433
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:58,874
and I got a grandson 35 years old.

434
00:23:58,979 --> 00:24:00,792
Come on, you're pulling my leg.

435
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:02,748
Why don't you just
give me a $10 bill?

436
00:24:02,749 --> 00:24:04,504
Here's the $5, and
five ones, there.

437
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:06,339
That way I won't be so quick
to see it break apart.

438
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:10,135
- Six children, huh? My, my, my...
- I've got a daughter, 51.

439
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:12,137
Oh, now, I don't mean to
be handing you no line,

440
00:24:12,242 --> 00:24:13,931
but that's just pretty hard to

441
00:24:13,932 --> 00:24:16,070
believe you got a
51-year-old child.

442
00:24:16,170 --> 00:24:17,559
You can believe it, all right.

443
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:20,979
Well, I'm afraid I'd have to see
it to believe it. Much obliged.

444
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:24,483
- See you again.
- You all come back.

445
00:24:37,934 --> 00:24:42,501
That just don't seem
quite right... somehow.

446
00:24:48,379 --> 00:24:49,379
Yes?

447
00:24:49,380 --> 00:24:51,343
I'm looking for Mr Stanley, madam.

448
00:24:51,448 --> 00:24:52,886
Mr Stanley's dead.

449
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:56,056
Oh, well, I'm looking for Mr
Warren M. Stanley, madam.

450
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:58,141
Warren's passed on, sir.

451
00:24:58,246 --> 00:24:59,392
Oh, that's hard to believe.

452
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:01,728
I was just talking to Warren
not more than two weeks back.

453
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:03,563
He ordered this
here bible from me.

454
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:05,941
Warren spent money on a bible?

455
00:25:06,046 --> 00:25:08,401
Yes, madam, with the name
Elvira in the corner.

456
00:25:08,507 --> 00:25:10,946
Why would Warren spend
money on a bible?

457
00:25:11,051 --> 00:25:12,948
He took fast to the idea, madam.

458
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:14,908
Only thing is, he left
a balance due of,

459
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:16,952
well, let's see, not counting
the dollar deposit...

460
00:25:17,057 --> 00:25:19,454
Daddy, this one's
already paid for.

461
00:25:20,685 --> 00:25:23,959
Mr Stanley paid for the whole
thing, don't you remember?

462
00:25:37,911 --> 00:25:39,933
Afternoon, madam. Mr Huff at home?

463
00:25:40,038 --> 00:25:42,769
Mr Huff passed away,
young man, a week ago.

464
00:25:42,874 --> 00:25:44,363
Oh, gee, I'm sorry.
I was just talking

465
00:25:44,364 --> 00:25:45,814
to Mr Huff not more
than a month ago.

466
00:25:45,919 --> 00:25:47,190
What was it you wanted?

467
00:25:47,295 --> 00:25:50,527
Oh, well, my name is Pray,
Kansas Bible Company.

468
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:53,113
Mr Huff ordered this bible as a
gift for someone named Edna.

469
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:55,115
Oh, that's my name.

470
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:56,754
You don't have to take
it if you don't want to.

471
00:25:56,755 --> 00:25:58,929
I'll just give you back Amos's
dollar deposit and then...

472
00:25:59,029 --> 00:26:01,371
Of course I want to keep it.

473
00:26:02,352 --> 00:26:04,207
He bought me a bible.

474
00:26:04,312 --> 00:26:06,501
Yes, madam. Now, I told Amos I
could sell him a cheaper one,

475
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:08,753
but no, naturally,
he wanted the best,

476
00:26:08,858 --> 00:26:11,131
the best, of course,
being the deluxe edition

477
00:26:11,236 --> 00:26:13,466
with the name printed in
child-in-the-manger gold letters,

478
00:26:13,572 --> 00:26:16,177
- bringing up a balance due of...
- of $24.

479
00:26:16,283 --> 00:26:18,555
$24. I'll get my purse.

480
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,307
What's your name, honey?

481
00:26:20,412 --> 00:26:23,435
- Addie.
- Addie. What a sweet little name.

482
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:24,686
Addie Pray, madam.

483
00:26:24,791 --> 00:26:28,189
Well, Addie Pray, I'm
going to give you $24,

484
